# Canonical project: principalai-credit-tool

- **Repository:** `sudipto-mo/principalai-credit-tool` — this is the GitHub repo that powers **Vercel** for **`www.principalai.pro`**.
- **Local path (reference):** `/Users/sudipto/Documents/Projects/principalai.pro/principalai-credit-tool`

## Where to edit

- **Full credit memo (single HTML):** `index.html` at the repo root.

## Workflow

- Run locally (static): `cd` to repo root, then `./serve.sh` (serves on **port 8080**) or `python3 -m http.server 8080`.
- **Do not `git commit` unless the user explicitly asks to commit** (e.g. “commit”, “commit and push”). Do not bundle `.cursor/` or other local-only IDE files into commits unless they explicitly ask to include them — keep those changes **local only**.
- **Do not `git push` (or push to GitHub) unless the user explicitly asks to push.** If they ask to push without having committed, confirm what to commit or ask them to say “commit” first.
- When they **do** ask to update GitHub / the live site: **commit and push to `origin main`** on **this** repo (only the files they intend — typically `index.html`, not `.cursor/` unless requested).
- **`principalai-app`** may contain a copy under `public/credit-memo/index.html` for the Next.js demo; treat it as **secondary** unless the user explicitly asks to sync that repo.

## Deploy

- Production follows **Vercel** deployments from **`main`** on **`principalai-credit-tool`**. After substantive HTML changes, the user (or an explicit “push” request) triggers **`git push`** and then confirm deployment in Vercel.
